{"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "schema", "document", "Document"], "kwargs": {"metadata": {"doc_id": "65a79b1e4586565ab55aed989bb2b3e8", "source": "NexaCorp Policy Handbook v5.2", "part": "6. Workplace Health & Safety", "section": "6.1 Safety Obligations & Responsibilities", "subsection": "6.1.2 Manager Responsibilities", "raw_content": "Conduct safety inductions for new team members within the first week of employment. Ensure safety rules are communicated, understood, and enforced within their team. Investigate and document all injuries and near-misses using the Incident Report Form (FAC-INC-01) within 24 hours. Conduct team safety audits quarterly and address identified hazards within 15 business days or escalate to Facilities with documented justification. Never pressure employees to continue work that they have identified as unsafe.", "type": "text"}, "page_content": "Part: 6. Workplace Health & Safety\n            Section: 6.1 Safety Obligations & Responsibilities\n            Subsection: 6.1.2 Manager Responsibilities\n            Conduct safety inductions for new team members within the first week of employment. Ensure safety rules are communicated, understood, and enforced within their team. Investigate and document all injuries and near-misses using the Incident Report Form (FAC-INC-01) within 24 hours. Conduct team safety audits quarterly and address identified hazards within 15 business days or escalate to Facilities with documented justification. Never pressure employees to continue work that they have identified as unsafe.", "type": "Document"}}